title: Baltimore County - Maryland logo
content: It reminds me of [Windsor](http://web.archive.org/web/20050516142536/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/urw/windsor/) or [Musketeer](http://web.archive.org/web/20050516142536/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/agfa/musketeer/)/Milton, but if one of those was used, it was only as a starting point for 'inspiration'. This has a rather 'mutilated' look to it, where width and maybe long distance legibilty, were apparently more important than esthetics.
author: bowfinpw
